---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service — aipm" description="Terms of service for aipm, the terminal-based AI project manager.">
  <div class="legal-content">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 25, 2025</p>

    <h2>Agreement</h2>
    <p>By using AIPM, you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, don't use it.</p>

    <h2>What AIPM Is</h2>
    <p>AIPM is an open-source, terminal-based AI project manager distributed under the MIT License. It runs locally on your machine.</p>

    <h2>License</h2>
    <p>AIPM is licensed under the MIT License. The full license text is available at <a href="https://github.com/ComputelessComputer/aipm/blob/main/LICENSE">github.com/ComputelessComputer/aipm/blob/main/LICENSE</a>. You are free to use, modify, and distribute AIPM in accordance with the MIT License.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>AIPM integrates with third-party services including Google APIs (Gmail, Calendar) and AI model providers (Anthropic, OpenAI).</li>
      <li>Your use of these services is subject to their respective terms of service and privacy policies.</li>
      <li>AIPM is not responsible for the availability, accuracy, or policies of third-party services.</li>
      <li>You are responsible for providing your own API keys and complying with the terms of the AI providers you use.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>API Keys & Credentials</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>AIPM requires API keys for AI functionality (Anthropic or OpenAI).</li>
      <li>You are responsible for securing your own API keys.</li>
      <li>AIPM stores API keys locally in its configuration directory on your machine.</li>
      <li>Do not share your API keys or AIPM configuration files containing them.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>AIPM is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, express or implied.</li>
      <li>We do not warrant that AIPM will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful components.</li>
      <li>AI-generated task suggestions and email filtering may contain errors or inaccuracies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To the maximum extent permitted by law, the maintainers of AIPM shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages.</li>
      <li>This includes damages for loss of data, profits, or goodwill arising from your use of AIPM.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your Responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You are responsible for the data you process through AIPM.</li>
      <li>You are responsible for reviewing AI-generated suggestions before acting on them.</li>
      <li>You must comply with all applicable laws when using AIPM.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Changes to Terms</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We may update these terms from time to time.</li>
      <li>Changes will be posted on this page with a revised date.</li>
      <li>Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>For questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:jeeheontransformers@gmail.com">jeeheontransformers@gmail.com</a></li>
      <li>For bug reports and feature requests: <a href="https://github.com/ComputelessComputer/aipm/issues">github.com/ComputelessComputer/aipm/issues</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-content {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-content h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .legal-content .last-updated {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .legal-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
  .legal-content p,
  .legal-content li {
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-secondary);
  }
  .legal-content ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-content a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
